# Creating a New Variant

1. Add a route folder under `src/app/<route>/` with `layout.tsx`, `page.tsx`, and `theme.module.css`.
2. Create `src/app/<route>/ui/` and add wrappers for needed primitives by importing from `[src/components/ui](mdc:src/components/ui)`.
3. Route components must import from `../ui/*`.
4. Keep styles and tokens in `theme.module.css` and reference them from local `ui` components.
5. Update `src/app/page.tsx` index if you want it listed.

Minimal wrapper template:

```tsx
// src/app/<route>/ui/input.tsx
import * as React from "react";
import { Input as Base } from "@/components/ui/input";

export const Input = React.forwardRef<HTMLInputElement, React.ComponentProps<typeof Base>>(function Input(props, ref) {
  return <Base ref={ref} className="rounded-md border-white/10 bg-white/5" {...props} />;
});
```

